The paper deals with a problem of making sequential decisions without feedback, which is a common topic in computer science. The problem involves probability distributions and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses optimal algorithms and bounds, which could place it in the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
